latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Classic evening glam in olive on @mrunu !
.
It’s so frikkin difficult to think of a new #makeuplook for someone like Mrunu who’s tried literally everything. All I had in mind was that I want the makeup look to be monotone, and not very colourful or graphic. When we started this one, we were gonna do plum eyes on her but mid-way she brought in some new eye palettes and I just couldn’t stop looking at this one olive shimmer! So, here’s how I can best describe the look - 
Shimmery eyes in olive and light gold tones - it’s a very underrated  combination and looks gorgeous on Indian skin. For the skin - we went dewy. And the lips, my favourite part - are overlined in a dark brown with a nude lipstick and a peach tint on top, and a tiny bit of gloss only on the Cupid’s bow and the centre of the lower lip. 
.
PRODUCTS USED - 
We mixed and matched a LOT, dipped the brushes in so many palettes and lip Colors that it’s kinda impossible to keep a track of what we used. A lot of these products were also from international brands which aren’t even available in india. So for this one, there are no product details 😕(I’m sorry again)
But tell me what you think of this look?
.

It takes a while to understand what Warm colors and cool colors  are, I still get confused sometimes - so this is the simplest way to understand this. Bronzer is more reddish brown and contour is more greyish brown. Makes sense?

Contour used - @cuffsnlashes cover pot 14 (it’s affordable long lasting and blends well, would recommend)
Bronzer used - @nykaabeauty foundation stick in shade 07 toffee chisel (light, blendable, long lasting, affordable, would recommend)

WHY YOU NEED A COLOR CORRECTOR:
.
2 reasons why your under eyes look gray/ashy -
1. You’re using a concealer way lighter than your complexion 
2. Your dark circles have bluish grey tones & you’re not neutralising that using a color corrector.
.
My recommendations:
@lagirlcosmetics Orange corrector 
@lagirlcosmetics Peach corrector (for fairer skin)
@mynykaa Skingenius conceal & correct palette - Deep 03 (the one I used in this video)
.
Concealer used @clinique_in Oat
.
#darkcircles #makeup #concealer #colorcorrection #makeup #makeuptutorial #mua #makeupartist #indianmua #wingitwithankush

How to contour & highlight your nose.
.
I’ve tried so many different viral hacks you see online but so many of them didn’t make sense. I realised #contouring has to be customised to every face. Also, a lot of those videos have filters on so there’s really no way to know if they work. I’ve come to realize the best way to understand how to contour is to understand your face and the natural shadows it casts. Understand your bone structure & contour accordingly. Also, don’t go berserk with nose contouring - it could look extremely unflattering in real life. 
.
I use the @mynykaa foundation stick in 07 toffee chisel as a contour stick. #notsponsored I genuinely love it. 
.

While so many men are still warming up to the idea of makeup, look at @gorgeouspotahto aka Shalakha totally rocking with this Korean eye makeup look inspired by Han Seo-Joon from #TrueBeauty on @primevideoin!
It is a story about a girl feeling empowered after wearing makeup and I think this story deserves to be heard! Watch it on Amazon Prime Video! 
.
About the look - while Han Seo-Joon wore a brown Smokey eye, we added a little tinge of red to add a little more drama to Karan’s look. We also did a minimal but very dewy base and a beautiful & glossy red ombré on his lips! What do you think? 
.
